Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @Chickpeas{1%400g can}; pat very dry with #paper towels{}.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces (halve lengthwise first if carrots are on the larger side). Halve, peel, and slice @Red Onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Peel and mince or grate @Ginger{1%thumb} until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4).

Toss chickpeas, carrots, and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}, @Curry Powder{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until chickpeas are crispy and veggies are tender, ~{18-22%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ginger, half the minced onion, @Garlic Powder{3/4%tsp}, @Garam Masala{3/4%tsp}, and a big pinch of salt (for 4 servings, use 1 1/2 tsp garlic powder and 1 1/2 tsp garam masala). (You'll use the rest of the garlic powder and garam masala later.) Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Basmati Rice{1/2%cup}, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{2}, and @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4). Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Mince @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}; transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Add @Red Pepper Jam{1}, remaining minced onion, remaining @Garlic Powder{1/4%tsp}, @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}, and @White Wine Vinegar{1/2%tbsp} (2 TBSP olive oil and 1 TBSP vinegar for 4 servings) to bowl.

Stir to combine; season with salt and pepper.

In a second small bowl, combine @Vegan Mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, remaining @Garam Masala{1/4%tsp}, @White Wine Vinegar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and @Sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4). (Be sure to measure the vinegar—we sent more!)

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in @Peas{4%ounce} and a drizzle of olive oil. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide rice and peas between #bowls{}; top with chickpeas and veggies. Drizzle with chutney and curry sauce. Serve.